  <refnamediv>
    <refname>plot_rimp</refname>
    <refpurpose>Plotting of impulsionnal response of a FIR filter</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   plot_rimp(h);
   plot_rimp(t,h,opt);
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>h:</term>
      <listitem><para> filter impulse vector (1d vector)</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>t:</term>
      <listitem><para> optionnal abcisse vector</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>opt:</term>
      <listitem><para> Optionnal parameters for the plot function (color / marker selections)</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
This function is just a wrapper around native <varname>plot2d3</varname> function, specialized for FIR coefficients display.
<refsection><title>Example</title></refsection>
<programlisting>
h = hilb(33); // Get Hilbert FIR filter approximation (33 coefs.)
clf(); plot_rimp(h);
</programlisting>
